channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden and Zelensky lay out new US support for Ukraine
item.description: US President Joe Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signed a new security agreement Thursday as world leaders gathered for the G7 summit in Italy. Follow here for the latest live news updates.

item.title: 9-year-old fatally shot in Milwaukee; city's 4th young gunshot victim in recent weeks
item.description: Police say a 9-year-old boy has become the fourth young gunshot victim in the city in recent weeks

item.title: Biden says he won't commute any sentence Hunter gets
item.description: President Biden already said he will not pardon his son, Hunter, which he reiterated during a joint news conference in Italy on Thursday.

item.title: Devastation in Gaza as Israel wages war on Hamas
item.description: US President Joe Biden said Thursday he is not confident that a ceasefire deal will be reached in Gaza soon, but added that he hasn't lost hope. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Trump yet to clarify his abortion pill policy as SCOTUS rules on mifepristone
item.description: As the Supreme Court upheld access to the abortion pill mifepristone in an unanimous decision, Donald Trump has yet to disclose his own abortion pill policy.

item.title: What a medication abortion is like, according to a doctor
item.description: An expert in medication abortion describes how mifepristone and misoprostol work and what to expect after using these medications known as the "abortion pill."

item.title: Clarence Thomas took 3 private jet trips provided by GOP donor, committee says
item.description: The Senate Judiciary Committee said it received documents showing Justice Clarence Thomas took three trips on a private jet provided by GOP megadonor Harlan Crow that had not been disclosed.

item.title: Trump in Washington for meetings with Republican allies
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is back in Washington for the first time since becoming the presumptive Republican nominee as well as a convicted felon. Follow here for the latest live news updates.
